The paper deals with the problem of pose estimation in autonomous navigation, which is a core topic in robotics (cs.RO). The proposed methodology involves fusing visual and inertial measurements, which are common in computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics. The use of optimization-based estimation methods is also common in machine learning (cs.LG) and control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper leverages the IMU preintegration method, which is a technique commonly used in robotics and computer vision (cs.AI).
